HTML Emmets/shortcuts
==============================

https://docs.emmet.io/cheat-sheet/

#div1 -> ID
.div2 -> class
ol>li*5{list-$}  -> Ordered list
ul>li*5{list-$} -> Un ordered list
table>tbody>tr*50>td*5{Data-$}

CSS types:
1. inline -> (style attribute) (restricted to an element)
    <div style="color:black; ">This is inline css div</div>
2. internal ->  (style tag/element) (restricted to 1 html page)
    <style>

    </style>
3. external css -> 
    1. write the css in a seperate .css file
    2. include that in htm;l file using <link>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="demo_1.css">

How to use bootstrap
    Add CDN link to the head of HTML file.
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">

How to write and execute Javascript code
========================================

1. Browser (frontend development)
    a. Create a javascript file with some javascript content
    b. Include that javascript file into html file using <Script> tag
2. NodeJS (Backend Developement)
    a. Run the created javascriot file in node environment in terminal
    works with document object, does not work with window object

Note: Every javascript code that runs on browser might not run in Node js

=======================

Most Commonly used Js functions:
    1. console.log()
        console: object log(): function
        Cannot use log() function directly without console
    2. document.write()
        document: object write(): function
        Cannot use write() function directly without console
    3. window.alert()
        window: object alert(): function
        Can use alert() directly because in global context/ with respect to brower everything is in wondow context
========================

Most commonly used Javascript object
    1. console : log(), error(), warn(), assert(), table(), time(), timeEnd()
    2. window : alert(), prompt(), confirm(), print(), close()
            a. alert() : Display message + ok
            b. confirm() : message + 2 buttons( ok(true), cancel(false))
            c. prompt() : message + text box + ok
    3. document : write(), writeln()
    4. Math : abs(), sqrt(), cbrt(), max(), min()
    5. Array : push(), pop(), filter(), map()
    6. Object : assign(), 